A minimalistic illustration of a single door split vertically down the middle—one half pristine white with a simple silver handle, the other half deep black with a golden ornate handle. Two distinct shadows stretch from the door onto a clean marble floor: one shadow is a crisp silhouette of a formal figure, the other is a translucent ghostly wisp fading into nothing. The composition uses stark negative space, with a subtle gradient background shifting from warm cream on the white door's side to cool charcoal on the black door's side. Clean geometric lines frame the scene.
